  "source": "// Dynamic take(n) example for durable state maps.\n// Demonstrates guarded unrolling: the compiler emits up to 64 guarded\n// iterations with a runtime check `if (i < n)` to avoid extra body runs.\n// First-release Kotodama fixes the iteration cap at 64.\n// Dynamic bounds are supported on state maps.\n\nseiyaku DynamicTake {\n  state Entries: Map<int, int>;\n\n  kotoage fn bounded_take_sum(n: int) -> int {\n    let acc = 0;\n    for (k, v) in Entries.take(n) {\n      // sum values deterministically\n      acc = acc + v;\n    }\n    return acc;\n  }\n}\n",
